<item>
            <title>[SOLR-12836] ZkController creates a cloud solr client with no connection or read timeouts</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-12836</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I found this while testing the changes in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-12739&quot; title=&quot;Make autoscaling policy based replica placement the default strategy for placing replicas&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-12739&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-12739&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The ZkController creates a SolrCloudManager with a new CloudSolrClient instance. However, no connection or read timeout is set for this CloudSolrClient. Therefore, when the policy framework tries to read freedisk metrics for a dead node (this is another bug), it just hangs forever causing collection APIs to timeout.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
